      <odd id="aspace_a3f5762cbfd6e81a62bb06e568504bf9">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 42-A (YRG 42-A), Records of military training programs.</p>  
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_5925b881a7403de9d1dcaa9af7ab74d1">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_02c2d34a6c10ddb5ace375df050c74a7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Signal Corps, Yale University, Records (RU 90). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_fe95dde36b2987ba56d9e52d9fe36921">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged alphabetically by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d6b62b949f6a81e7c36c6c8d8a1b3c39">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Signal Corps School for Officer Candidates was established at Yale in 1918.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_9039247dc24537fdaa1e7b60400ec464">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, reports, course descriptions, financial records, and personnel files documenting the Signal Corps School for Officer Candidates at Yale.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
